:R-HSA-1483213  a           owl:NamedIndividual , obo:GO_0006646 ;
        rdfs:comment        "<i>De novo</i> (Kennedy pathway) synthesis of phosphatidylethanolamine (PE) involves phosphorylation of ethanolamine (ETA) to phosphoethanolamine (PETA) followed by condensing with cytidine triphosphate (CTP) to form CDP-ethanolamine (CDP-ETA). Diacylglycerol (DAG) and CDP-ETA together then form PE. Alternatively, PE is formed when phosphatidylserine (PS) is decarboxylated by phosphatidylserine decarboxylase proenzyme (PISD) (Henneberry et al. 2002, Vance 1991, Vance 1990)." ;
        rdfs:label          "Synthesis of PE" ;
        dc:contributor      "Edited: Williams, MG, 2011-08-12" , "Authored: Williams, MG, 2011-09-14" , "Reviewed: Wakelam, Michael, 2012-05-14" , "GOC:reactome_curators" ;
        dc:date             "2026-06-29" ;
        pav:providedBy      "https://reactome.org" ;
        oboInOwl:hasDbXref  "R-HSA-1483213" ;
        skos:narrower       <http://model.geneontology.org/R-HSA-1483206/R-HSA-1483206> ;
        skos:note           "org.biopax.paxtools.model.level3.Pathway" .

